'''Absurdity''', ''<code>[[noun (part of speech)|noun]]</code>''; ''[[pl (source)|pl]].'' '''Absurdities''' ([[-t&ibreve;z]]). [L. ''absurditas'': cf. F. ''absurdite''.]

<ol>
<li>The quality of being absurd or [[inconsistent]] with [[obvious]] truth, reason, or sound judgment.

<code>The ''absurdity'' of the actual idea of an infinite number.</code> ''[[Locke (source)|Locke]].''

<li> That which is absurd; an absurd action; a [[logical]] [[contradiction]].

<code>His travels were full of ''absurdities''. ''[[Johnson (source)|Johnson]].''</code>
</ol>